cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IR. 

This paper is about cost and cardinality estimation in query optimization, which is a core problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes an end-to-end learning-based framework based on deep learning, which involves feature extraction, encoding, and a tree-structured model. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with string values and predicate matching, which are relevant to cs.IR (information retrieval).
